title: Legacy Mode
description: AnyShake Explorer currently has two data transmission protocols, legacy mode and mainline mode, which are used to transmit data to the AnyShake Observer. The mainline mode is the default mode, which is more stable and efficient, compatible with AnyShake Observer v3.2.2 and higher version. The legacy mode is an old version of the data transmission protocol, which is compatible with all versions of AnyShake Observer.
